<tr><td class='easySpoilerRow' colspan='2' style=''><div id='spoilerDiv139c8001' class='easySpoilerSpoils'  style='display:none; white-space:wrap; overflow:auto; vertical-align:middle;'>
</p>
<p>At first this looks absurdly easy &#8212; surely promoting either white pawn leads directly to mate?</p>
<p>The trouble is that once either pawn advances, the other is pinned and can&#8217;t move. Instead, the key is the crazy-looking 1. Qh7! Black&#8217;s rook has no safe refuge on the eighth rank, and if it takes the queen then a pawn promotion is fatal.</p>
<p>From <em>The Problemist</em>, 1941.</p>
<p>07/29/2025 My description isn&#8217;t quite accurate &#8212; a few readers have pointed out that Black&#8217;s rook is safe on b8. In that case White can mate with 2. Nc7, a smothered checkmate. Thanks to everyone who wrote in about this.</p>
<p>
